Pathway Name: Citrate cycle (TCA cycle) - Cyanothece sp. ATCC 51142
Pathway Class:  Carbohydrate metabolism

Pathway Description: The citrate cycle (TCA cycle, Krebs cycle) is an important aerobic pathway for the final steps of the oxidation of carbohydrates and fatty acids. The cycle starts with acetyl-CoA, the activated form of acetate, derived from glycolysis and pyruvate oxidation for carbohydrates and from beta oxidation of fatty acids.
